              <span>View this object's location on our interactive map</span>
            </a>
          </dd>
        
                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Hanging scroll; gold on silk</dd>
            
           
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>painting proper: 90.4 x 79.3 cm (35 9/16 x 31 1/4 in.)<br />
mounting, including cord and roller ends: 192.8 x 101.3 cm (75 7/8 x 39 7/8 in.)<br />
scroll mounting: 187.8 x 94.8 cm (73 15/16 x 37 5/16 in.)<br />
110 x 13.5 x 14.2 cm (43 5/16 x 5 5/16 x 5 9/16 in.) (storage, Box)</dd>
            
            
            
            
            
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>[James J. Freeman, Kyoto, (by 1976)], sold; to Sylvan Barnet and William Burto, Cambridge, MA, (1976-2014), gift from Sylvan Barnet and bequest from William Burto; to the Harvard Art Museums, 2014.</dd>
        
        
        
        <dt>Acquisition and Rights</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Credit Line</dt>
              <dd>Harvard Art Museums/Arthur M. Sackler Museum, Gift of Sylvan Barnet and William Burto in honor of John M. Rosenfield</dd>
            
            
                          <dt>Accession Year</dt>
              <dd>2014</dd>
            
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>2014.139</dd>

